  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed development, by reason of the height, scale and detailed design of the proposed acoustic screens, would represent an overly dominant and visually discordant feature on the host building and terrace of which it forms part when viewed from the private realm. This would harm the appearance of the original building, fail to preserve the character and appearance of The Angel Conservation Area and harm the significance of the setting of the Grade II listed terrace of no's 31 to 45 Camden Passage, with no public benefit to outweigh this harm. Thie proposal is therefore contrary to policy HC1 of the London Plan (2021), policies CS8 and CS9 of Islington's Core Strategy (2011), policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of Islington's Development Management Policies as well as the guidance of The Angel Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002) and Islington's Urban Design Guide (2017)."
